spirit:component.spirit:name: bd_soc_system_ila_0_0
spirit:component.spirit:description: The System ILA core is a customizable logic analyzer core that can be used to monitor a combination of AXI based interfaces and individual signals. This core extend the features of basic ILA for easier debugging at a system level. This includes Boolean trigger equations, customizable data capture buffer depth and optional trigger input/output ports at both signal level as well as for interfaces. The System ila core is synchronous to the design being monitored and hence all clock constraints that are applied to your design are also applied to the components inside the core. Run-time interaction with this core requires the use of Vivado Logic Analyzer feature.
